text: Miloud Rebiaï (born December 12, 1993, in Tlemcen) is an Algerian footballer who plays for MC Alger in the Algerian Ligue Professionnelle 1. On March 24, 2012, Rebiaï made his professional debut for WA Tlemcen, coming on a substitute in a league match against MC Saïda. ==References== ==External links== * * Category:1993 births Category:Algerian footballers Category:Algerian Ligue Professionnelle 1 players Category:Algerian Ligue Professionnelle 2 players Category:Algeria youth international footballers Category:ES Sétif players Category:Living people Category:People from Tlemcen Category:WA Tlemcen players Category:Footballers at the 2016 Summer Olympics Category:Olympic footballers of Algeria Category:Association football fullbacks
